  <mainDescription>Many organizations have an internal Security team that is responsible for protecting their IT systems and data from&#xD;
malicious attacks and ensuring that the organization is not exposed to a security risk. Each Security team typically has a&#xD;
Security Lead who is responsible for establishing the processes and standards for ensuring the security of the IT systems&#xD;
that they are responsible for.</mainDescription>
  <skills>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A person&amp;nbsp;filling this role should have these skills:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Deep knowledge of security testing approaches and techniques&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Very good understanding of the industry standards and regulations&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Intimate knowledge of the types of systems or applications&amp;nbsp;under test, or both&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Knowledge of the networking architecture&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Very good&amp;nbsp;knowledge of the test automated security tools&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></skills>
  <assignmentApproaches>This role is typically held by an individual with many years of experience as a security professional who has a deep&#xD;
understanding of the current security trends.</assignmentApproaches>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
